s Will Steer A Smaller Printer Company |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/amyfeldman/2019/10/04/spotlight-on-hp-incoming-ceo-enrique-lores-as-the-printer-giant-announces-a-restructuring-and-plans-to-cut-up-to-9000-jobs/ |accessdate=2 November 2019 |work=Forbes |date=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n*[[Ramon Laguarta]] (born 1964), CEO of [[PepsiCo]]\n\n*[[Josep Maria Bartomeu]] (born 1963), President of [[FC Barcelona]]\n\n*[[Ferran Soriano]] (born 1967), CEO of [[Manchester City F.C.]]\n\n*[[Gabriel Escarrer Jaume]] (born 1971), Billionaire Founder and CEO of [[Meli\u00e1 Hotels International]]\n\n*[[Joan Rigol]] (born 1943), former president of the [[Parliament of Catalonia]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.esade.edu/ ESADE Official Website]\n\n[[Category:ESADE|Business School]]\n[[Category:Business schools in Spain]]\n[[Category:Education in Barcelona]]\n[[Category:Business schools in Europe]]\n[[Category:Jesuit universities and colleges in Spain]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1958]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox University\n |name              = '''ESADE Business School'''\n |native_name       = \n |image_name        = [[File:COM4EU-prtnr-ESADE.png|200px]]\n |image_size        = 100px\n |caption           = \n |motto             = Inspiring Futures.\n |mottoeng          = \n |established       = 1958\n |type              = [[Private university|Private]] [[Business School]]\n |dean              = Alfons Sauquet\n |director          = Eug\u00e8nia Bieto Caubet\n |faculty           = \n |staff             = \n |students          = 7674<ref name=\"Annual Report\">{{cite web|url=http://itemsweb.esade.edu/wi/documentos/web/memoria_eng2012.pdf |title=ESADE Annual Report |accessdate=15 July 2013 |publisher=ESADE}}</ref>\n |undergrad         = \n |postgrad          = \n |doctoral          = \n |other             = \n |city              = [[Barcelona]]\n |province          = [[Catalonia]]\n |country           = Spain\n |